{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 3 presents our main results.",
    "Models trained with a mix of relevant and random documents (M gr) perform best when provided with either gold or mixed contexts.",
    "This suggests that mixing relevant and random contexts during training can enhance the generator's robustness to irrelevant information while ensuring effective utilization of relevant contexts.",
    "Therefore, we identify the practice of augmenting with a few relevant and randomly-selected documents during training as the best approach.",
    "Detailed dataset information, hyperparameters and experimental results can be found in Appendix A.5."
  ]
}